Program: Outlook
Title: I Died Six Times on my Honeymoon
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01g0nfp
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 10 Sep 2013
The British man who died six times when he was on honeymoon in the Maldives. Also, Jonathan Holiff talks about his father who was Johnny Cash's former manager. We talk to the 25-year-old entrepreneur who started the only dry cleaning business in Mogadishu, and former Chinese-Zimbabwean politician Fay Chung and her daughter, Chipo, join us to discuss their experiences of growing up in Zimbabwe. Show less